## Purpose

This folder is the **Living Design Agent Kit**: agent-readable rules that help tools generate UI that correctly uses Living Design components, tokens, and patterns.

## Non-Negotiables

- **MUST** use existing Living Design components first. Do not re-implement common UI primitives (Button, Input, Modal, etc.) if a Living Design component exists.
- **MUST** use Living Design tokens (CSS variables) for all visual styling: color, typography, spacing, radius, shadows, motion.
- **MUST NOT** hardcode hex colors, pixel sizes, font sizes, radii, or shadows.
- **MUST NOT** invent token names or component APIs. If missing, stop and ask.
- **MUST** ensure accessibility: keyboard support, focus visibility, semantic HTML, ARIA where needed.

## React-Specific Rules

- **MUST NOT** use components marked `@private` in JSDoc.
- **MUST NOT** use plain HTML text elements (`<p>`, `<span>`, `<h1>`) without Living Design typography components when available.
- **MUST NOT** use Tailwind typography classes (`text-lg`, `font-bold`, etc.) or hardcode font-size/weight/line-height.
- **MUST NOT** reference CSS tokens directly in application code (use component props instead).
- **MUST** use Living Design typography components (Display, Heading, Body, Caption) when available.
- **MUST** configure typography through component props (`size`, `weight`, `as`).
- **MUST** use semantic HTML via the `as` prop.

```tsx
// CORRECT
<Body as="p" size="medium" weight="default">Body text.</Body>
<Heading as="h2" size="large" weight="default">Section Title</Heading>

// WRONG
<p className="text-base">Text</p>
<span style={{ fontSize: '16px' }}>Text</span>
```

## Decision Tree

1. **Need UI styling?** Start with token rules: see [DesignTokens.md](./DesignTokens.md).
2. **Need a UI element?** Check [ComponentReference.md](./ComponentReference.md) and [Component-Inventory.md](./Component-Inventory.md).
3. **Need component guidelines?** Check `guidelines/components/[ComponentName].md`.

